1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,290
If I ask about your job,

2
00:00:01,290 --> 00:00:05,115
you may say that I'm a doctor, I'm an
engineer, I'm an accountant, I'm a lawyer.

3
00:00:05,115 --> 00:00:10,560
You will say all these things, but
actually your job is, can you guess?

4
00:00:11,780 --> 00:00:12,958
You are a servant.

5
00:00:12,958 --> 00:00:14,694
I can't use the other word.

6
00:00:14,694 --> 00:00:19,171
If you are not offended, then I will say,
you are a slave of your mind.

7
00:00:19,171 --> 00:00:20,330
That's what you do.

8
00:00:20,330 --> 00:00:23,465
You didn't want to go to school, you know
that.

9
00:00:23,465 --> 00:00:26,677
You wanted to play, but you had to go to
school.

10
00:00:26,677 --> 00:00:29,406
You had to get good education, and you got
it.

11
00:00:29,406 --> 00:00:30,824
You got your PhD.

12
00:00:30,824 --> 00:00:33,356
With that certificate, you applied for a
job.

13
00:00:33,356 --> 00:00:34,391
Then you found it.

14
00:00:34,391 --> 00:00:36,886
And you start your journey from there.

15
00:00:36,886 --> 00:00:38,264
You started earning money.

16
00:00:38,264 --> 00:00:40,020
did you do with that money?

17
00:00:40,020 --> 00:00:42,239
How much money do you have in your account
now?

18
00:00:42,239 --> 00:00:44,789
Each time you earn money, you had to
spend.

19
00:00:44,789 --> 00:00:48,989
Because when you see something, when you
hear something, your mind is vexed.

20
00:00:48,989 --> 00:00:50,402
Because you think that,

21
00:00:50,402 --> 00:00:54,698
that movie, that picture, that scenery,
whatever it is, it's so pleasurable.

22
00:00:54,698 --> 00:00:55,892
That's how you thought.

23
00:00:55,892 --> 00:01:00,140
As soon as you think about it, your mind
is vexed.
